edit: Ryu since we are running the same operating system this is what I did and had no problems with it. I went to the start menu and clicked on Window's Update. (it's in the top part of your first start menu). One the web page that pops up, click on Product Update. Then check DX 8.1 patch (about 5 to 10 mins depending on your processer speed and internet connection). It will restart your computer and then you'll be all set. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Oh on a side note. Don't be surprised if you have to run it a couple of times, it froze on me three times as I tried to download it...but you know what Windows says, it's a feature when their downloads freeze your system.<br>
<br>
On a side note:<br>
I found out a way to bandage my computer so it can run for the next 5 years and not be too out of date. So for all you out there with systems as old as mine (hint I had Win 95 installed on it when I bought it), go find you a little tech shop in the town where you live. Talk to them about an upgrade package. The one I'm going to said they can gut my old system (I have lots of nice toys attached to it that I have upgraded over the years) put them on the new mother board with a new processer (Whoot! no more PII 333mhz processer, I can finally make it into the next century) and in a new tower for under $300.00. (price will depend on the processer you buy. I'm going with the AMD 1.0 gig or maybe the 1.1 gig processor.) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
That is way cheaper than the new computers I was looking into, and I can still use my fairly good video card (Radan &lt;sp&gt; 32mb PCI) and keep my Windows 98 SE (which means I can keep my scanner and not have to shell out anymore money on a new Windows product). <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
This is just what I'm going to do. Just told you guys in case there is someone out there with an old system like me who can't shell out $1000.00 on a new system.<br>
